==English==

===Etymology===
From [[localize]] + [[-ation]]; compare French ''[[localisation#French|localisation]]''

===Alternative spellings===
* [[localisation]] (''British'')

===Noun===
'''localization'''  (''plural:'' '''[[localizations]]''')
# The act of [[localize|localizing]].
# The [[state]] of being localized.
# (''software engineering'') The act or process of making a product [[suitable]] for use in a particular country or [[region]], typically by [[translating]] text into the [[language]] of that country or region and, if necessary, ensuring support of non-Latin [[character set]]s.  Abbreviation: [[l10n]] ''(numerals one and zero, for the number of characters between the 'L' and 'N' usually in lowercase.)''

